column2: Windy- no whitecaps-sunny-loon showed up to watch.
Ice off last weekend- 50 degrees today.  Partly sunny-pair of loons out all morning.
Partly sunny today- ice off in the last weekend.  A pair of loons around all morning.
Macroinvertebrates in bottom sample (27')- loons present- 80 degrees outside- duck with babies.
65 degrees outside- 1 loon- 1 long leg neck bird (heron )- at a chipmunk by our dock- slight wind.
Algal mats on one side of the lake only- 3 loons and 8 seagulls- 88 degrees outside- aquatic plant survey done this week- I have an internship position with Northern Lake Service.
Water clarity reduced-algae- 8" rain- polluting tamarack bog rushing into our lake via a drain pipe-very upsetting!
Ice on in swamp.  30 degrees outside- some aquatic vegetation still green and growing.
3 loons- sunny 60 degrees- ice off 3 weeks ago.  Sampled during bright sun.
Windy- 48 deg F. Pair of loons present.
Slightly windy- partly cloudy. Eagle sighted catching a fish.
Partly cloudy- high traffic. Loons with one hatchling sighted.
Mostly sunny. Pair of loons and one offspring present.
50 deg F- sunny and windy. Beautiful day- leaves just beyond peak and falling. Brief snow yesterday. Equipment failure- sampler broke- got phosphorus- chlorophyll- and 3 DO samples only
One loon watched us.  65 F outside.
sunny- and white caps.  No freshwater jellyfish talked about or spotted this summer.
It was partly cloudy and windy.  Two loons were spotted and the water clarity was good.
The sky was partly cloudy and the wind was calm.  There was a lot of pollen floating in the air.
partly cloudy- windy 10mph- temperature was 50 degrees.
sunny- clear sky with no wind- glassy waters.
very windy- whitecaps- full sun- 80 degrees
calm- glassy water- sunny and warm
